I've learned this through experience, being the only active wiz at the end of a raid when there arn't enough people to port means you end up translocating a BUNCH of people, and THEN porting out a full group.  Not fun if a mob pops after most have left already.<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
Level 56 Wizard<br>
The Nameless Server<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uariachne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>ariachne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/1/01 10:31:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dissed by my own guild...</span><hr size=1> Hmmm,<br>
<br>
     I have to say, I spent alot of time in DL for the experience grind, as I am sure everyone else has.  I am a mage, and no way I could get a group there, I would LFG forever.  My most frequent partner is a wizard the same level, we grab a cleric and the three of us would rock, and yeah the cleric pulled, we dropped the bad guys fast enough, he didn't have to heal a whole lot.  Whenever we saw a caster LFG, we grabbed them up.  It wasn't long before we had a full group of casters that would tear up anything the cleric would bring to us.  And we never go out of mana, hell it takes one nuke each.  Pretty soon everyone wants in our group.  We kept it to caster groups, with our cleric (Actually the wiz, the cleric and I pretty much travel as a set).  My advice is you may never know why your guild members didn't invite you, specualtion will get you no where, but you can do something about thegroup situation.  Everytime you see a fellow caster LFG, grab them.  Hell my wizzie friend is one awesome puller/tank (hope he doesn't read that).  Caster groups rock and you do have a choice to be in one.  You see 3 wizzies looking for group? That is a group.  You know, prior to level 44, when most casters come into their own so to speak, my guild's opinion of casters wasn't all that high.  We grabbed a tank or two from the guild and put them in our caster groups with us to show them what we could do.  Our tanks now always want the casters along, and have a new respect for what they call (not us) firepower (and they mean us as people not just our spells).  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/usarxosthesorcerer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarxos the Sorcerer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/1/01 3:49:46 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.eqiceni.co.uk/members/sarxossmall1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dissed by my own guild...</span><hr size=1> Aye, certainly out of order to be asked to go and pick up a replacement for a group who you are waiting to join, and they KNOW you are waiting to join them, just because you can port and they didnt want you.<br>
<br>
In my opinion, just tell the guild on open guild channel that they had better not do that again and that if they have a problem with grouping with you or a wizard they should tell you now or shut the f**k up and NEVER do that to you again. I wouldnt beat around the bush, best to be staight and to the point. That way they know where they stand with you.<br>
